Subject: [PATCH] clus: fix dangling reference to BGL named-parameter temporaries

The Boost.Graph named-parameter object built by

    weight_map(get(boost::edge_weight, m_graph))
        .predecessor_map(&predecessors[0])
        .distance_map(&distances[0])

is a chain of bgl_named_params temporaries: each .foo_map() call returns a new
bgl_named_params *by value* that holds a reference to the previous link in the
chain. Binding the final link to `const auto& param` lifetime-extends only that
last temporary -- the earlier links it references are destroyed at the end of
the full expression. `param` therefore dangles by the time it is handed to
boost::dijkstra_shortest_paths() on the following statement.

GCC 13+ correctly flags this with -Wdangling-reference; it is promoted to a hard
error under Wire-Cell's release -Werror. (This is a genuine latent
use-after-free, not the boost::multi_array false positive seen elsewhere.)

Fix: pass the named-parameter chain directly as the call argument, so every
temporary in the chain lives for the full duration of the dijkstra call.

Upstream target: wirecell/wire-cell-toolkit, file clus/src/Graphs.cxx.
Reproduce: a release-mode build under GCC >= 13. No behavior change.
---
 clus/src/Graphs.cxx | 9 +++++----
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

--- a/clus/src/Graphs.cxx	2026-06-18 11:34:56.343112337 -0700
+++ b/clus/src/Graphs.cxx	2026-06-18 11:35:24.787498476 -0700
@@ -222,10 +222,11 @@
     std::vector<size_t> predecessors(nvtx); 
     std::vector<Weighted::dijkstra_distance_type> distances(nvtx);
 
-    const auto& param = weight_map(get(boost::edge_weight, m_graph))
-                       .predecessor_map(&predecessors[0])
-                       .distance_map(&distances[0]);
-    boost::dijkstra_shortest_paths(m_graph, source, param);
+    boost::dijkstra_shortest_paths(
+        m_graph, source,
+        weight_map(get(boost::edge_weight, m_graph))
+            .predecessor_map(&predecessors[0])
+            .distance_map(&distances[0]));
 
     // Add to front of access order list
     m_access_order.push_front(source);
